name: methyl 6-methylnicotinate

The two methyl groups are alkyl substituents and would commonly add a smaller incremental increase due to greater van der Waals forces from the increased molecular weight and surface area, usually estimated at about +5 to +10 degrees Celsius each. However, one of the methyl groups is attached to the nitrogen-containing ring, which may somewhat modulate this effect. This leads to a total predicted melting point shift relative to benzene of +60 degrees Celsius.
